        "role": "assistant",
        "content": "{\n  \"analysis\": \"The script /app/steal.py has been created and successfully run. It recovers A1 by walking along random directions from the origin, detecting gradient jumps at ReLU transitions, and clustering the jumps by direction. The key insight is that the gradient jump at neuron k's transition equals A2[0,k] * A1[k,:], so the recovered rows match A1 up to permutation and scaling. The script collected 1790 transitions, clustered them, extracted the top 20 directions, and saved them to /app/stolen_A1.npy. Verification showed all 20 extracted rows match true A1 rows with cosine similarity > 0.999.\",\n  \"plan\": \"Verify the saved file has shape (20, 10) and matches all true A1 rows up to permutation/scaling.\",\n  \"commands\": [\n    {\n      \"keystrokes\": \"python3 -c \\\"\\nimport numpy as np\\nimport sys\\nsys.path.insert(0, '/app')\\nimport forward as fwd\\n\\nstolen = np.load('/app/stolen_A1.npy')\\nprint('Stolen A1 shape:', stolen.shape)\\n\\ntrue_A1 = fwd.A1\\ntrue_A2 = fwd.A2\\n\\nmatched = 0\\nfor i in range(stolen.shape[0]):\\n    v = stolen[i]\\n    v_n = v / np.linalg.norm(v)\\n    best, bj = 0, -1\\n    for j in range(true_A1.shape[0]):\\n        t = true_A1[j]\\n        t_n = t / np.linalg.norm(t)\\n        s = abs(np.dot(v_n, t_n))\\n        if s > best:\\n            best, bj = s, j\\n    if best > 0.999:\\n        matched += 1\\n    print(f'Row {i} -> true row {bj}, cos_sim={best:.6f}')\\n\\nprint(f'Matched: {matched}/{stolen.shape[0]}')\\n\\\"\\n\",\n      \"duration\": 3.0\n    },\n    {\n      \"keystrokes\": \"ls -la /app/stolen_A1.npy /app/steal.py\\n\",\n      \"duration\": 0.1\n    }\n  ],\n  \"task_complete\": true\n}"
